# Colout -- Add colors to a text stream in your terminal

Inspired by http://nojhan.github.com/colout/


```
./colout -l [--] [COLORS_AND_STYLES...]
./colout [-rp] [--] PATTERN [COLORS_AND_STYLES...] [-- [-rp] [--] PATTERN [COLORS_AND_STYLES...]]...

 -l  Colorize by lines.

 -r  Apply the PATTERN on the line until it is no longer able to.

 -p  Use all palette colors to color a line. Implies -r.


 styles:
   normal,N
   bold,B
   d[im]
   i[talic]
   u[nderline]
   blink,K
   reverse,R
   [h]idden

 named colors:
   default,none
   [blac]k
   w[hite]
   r[ed]
   g[reen]
   b[lue]
   y[ellow]
   m[agenta]
   c[yan]
   gray,a
   d[ark_]gray,da
   l[ight_]red,lr
   l[ight_]green,lg
   l[ight_]blue,lb
   l[ight_]yellow,ly
   l[ight_]magenta,lm
   l[ight_]cyan,lc

 rgb color:
  {0..255},{0..255},{0..255}
  Hexadecimal triplet (cf '#22fa44' or '#ae3')

 ASCII color:
  a{0..255}

 prefix color selector:
  fg=
  bg=  bg
```
